> Instead of going the traditional route with these tacos, we decided to mix things up with a Korean-style sesame beef filling. The filling gets a kick from gochugaru—chili flakes traditionally used in dishes like kimchi and bulgogi. It's an unconventional choice, perhaps, but one that lives up to the maxim that everything tastes better in a tortilla.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @radishes{3}(trimmed and thinly sliced into rounds) and @Persian cucumber{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced into rounds). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(leaves picked from stems).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine radishes, cucumber, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 1 tsp @sugar{2.5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Taste and add a pinch more sugar if you like a sweeter pickle. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and a pinch of @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (taste and add more from there if desired; save a little for steps 4 and 6). Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallions and @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and 1 tsp sugar (2 tsp for 4 servings). Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, half the @Sriracha{2%teaspoon} (you'll use more later), and a pinch of chili flakes to taste. Taste and season with salt, pepper, and up to ½ tsp more sugar.

While filling cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Spread a bit of chili sour cream onto each tortilla; top with beef filling, a bit of pickled veggies, and cilantro leaves. Add as much remaining sriracha and chili flakes as you like. Serve with any remaining pickled veggies on the side.